    <h1 class="font center" style="font-size:24px">
        Know Your Surroundings:
                <br />

Familiarize yourself with Night City's districts, neighborhoods, and their associated risks. Understand which areas are controlled by gangs, corporate interests, or law enforcement. Recognize safe zones, shadowy alleys, and locations notorious for criminal activities. Knowledge of the city's geography will allow you to plan routes, identify escape routes, and avoid dangerous areas.
                <br />
        <br />

Choose Your Allies Wisely:
                <br />

In Night City, trust is a scarce commodity. Surround yourself with trustworthy individuals who can watch your back. Build relationships with fixers, reliable contacts, and street-smart locals who can provide valuable information and assistance when needed. However, always be cautious and remain vigilant for potential betrayal or double-crosses.
                <br />
        <br />

Adapt to the Street Code:
                <br />

Understanding and adhering to the unspoken rules of the streets is crucial. Respect the hierarchy, show deference to powerful figures, and avoid unnecessary conflicts. Keep a low profile when needed, but be ready to assert yourself when necessary. Learning the subtle nuances of Night City's street code will help you navigate social interactions and minimize potential confrontations.
                <br />
        <br />

Enhance Your Skills:
                <br />

Develop a diverse set of skills that align with the demands of Night City. Whether it's combat proficiency, hacking abilities, stealth tactics, or negotiation skills, honing your talents will provide you with a significant advantage. Invest in cyberware enhancements, acquire specialized gear, and constantly improve your abilities to handle the challenges that await you.
                <br />
        <br />

Master Cybersecurity:
                <br />

In a city ruled by technology, cybersecurity is paramount. Protect yourself from data breaches, hacks, and cyber attacks by equipping advanced security software and firewalls. Stay updated on the latest threats and vulnerabilities, and develop your knowledge of hacking techniques to defend against potential cyber threats. Remember, in Night City, your personal data is a valuable asset that can be exploited.
    </h1>
